The joint statement by North American leaders emphasizes the importance of economic cooperation and the need for broad-based, sustainable economic growth and job creation. They discuss their commitment to reducing regulatory differences and improving the business environment, as well as securing supply chains and efficient borders. The leaders also pledge to protect and enforce intellectual property rights, enhance energy cooperation, and work towards a lasting global solution to climate change. They recognize the importance of an open, secure, and reliable internet, and commit to strengthening security in the Americas and supporting Haiti's development. The leaders also highlight their strengthened dialogue on priority issues and their commitment to working together within the Inter-American System and the VI Summit of the Americas. They acknowledge the value of promoting growth and trade for global economic recovery and express support for the Mexican Presidency of the G-20. Finally, they welcome Mexico's offer to host the next North American Leaders' Summit.